state_summary: The article discusses the trends and expectations for startups and venture capital investors in 2026, highlighting the importance of AI, global markets, and new technologies.
evidence: Raising in 2025 requires a shift from 'visionary' to 'battle-tested.'
Founders must prove to VCs they have more than just traction; they need a distribution advantage.
The bar is rising for founders to stand out with unique distribution channels or perspectives.
Capital moats have already formed around crowded sectors.
We expect investor and startup interest to continue at all-time highs.
AI will stop being a separate category, as it will just be a part of all new technology companies being built.
